This is my README file.
ServiceNow Integration doesnt want to play nice with additional files that I add -- which are NOT part of SNOW instance.
Attempts to Sync up the code on the public Developer Instance with the GitHub project resulted in deletion of pre-existing files.
To save developer specific notes that I create or discover, need a safe and relatable side-project with similar name.

Most Important / Immediately Useful Article on PDF Generator:
https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=4acc6265dbd0dbc01dcaf3231f961949

----------

You can assign SNOW Table fields to PDF fields and dynamically insert values into the PDF.
However this PDF MUST already exist as a Managed Document within SNOW.
AND the PDF MUST be a "fillable PDF".

Dynamic PDFs and SNOW Tables
-----------------------------
https://docs.servicenow.com/bundle/kingston-hr-service-delivery/page/product/human-resources/concept/c_HRDocumentTemplates.html#generate-pdf

Fillable PDFs
--------------------
https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/how-to/convert-word-excel-paper-pdf-forms.html
** Apparently needs licensed copy of Acrobat.
** Allows conversion of an Existing WORD doc to a Fillable PDF.
